message.content: If Max paid $10\%$ of the cost of the bike upfront, and the upfront payment was $\$150$, then the total cost of the bike is $100\% - 10\% = 90\%$ of the upfront payment.  Since $90\%$ of $\$150$ is $\frac{90}{100} \times \$150 = \$\frac{90}{100} \times 150 = \frac{9}{10} \times 150 = \frac{9}{2} \times 15 = 9 \times 15 = \boxed{135}$ dollars, the price of the bike was $\boxed{\$135}$.
